acteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":38,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir John de Burghersh, Knt was born on 29 September 1343, in Ewelme, Oxfordshire, England, his father, John de Burghersh, was 19 and his mother, Maud de Kerdeston, was 26. He married Ismania Lady Baroness Kerdeston deHanham in 1372, in Gloucestershire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. His occupation is listed as sheriff in Somerset, England, United Kingdom. He died on 21 September 1391, in his hometown, at the age of 47, and was buried in Ewelme, Oxfordshire, England."},"et":{"29 September 1343–21 September 1391":"29. september 1343–21. september 1391","1343–1391":"1343–1391","1335–1420":"1335–1420","1379–1437":"1379–1437","–1421":"–1421","1324–1349":"1324–1349","1318–1349":"1318–1349","30 June 1349":"30. juuni 1349","30